# Applying Brand Guidelines Skill

Apply consistent corporate branding and styling to all generated documents.

## Brand Configuration Structure

```json
{
  "brand": {
    "name": "Company Name",
    "tagline": "Your tagline here",
    "colors": {
      "primary": "#3B82F6",
      "secondary": "#10B981",
      "accent": "#F59E0B",
      "neutral": { "50": "#F8FAFC", "900": "#0F172A" }
    },
    "typography": {
      "fontFamily": { "display": "Inter", "body": "Inter", "mono": "JetBrains Mono" },
      "fontSize": { "xs": "0.75rem", "base": "1rem", "4xl": "2.25rem" }
    },
    "voice": {
      "tone": ["Professional", "Approachable", "Innovative"],
      "doNot": ["Use jargon", "Be condescending", "Overpromise"]
    }
  }
}
```

## CSS Variables Generation

```css
:root {
  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
  --color-secondary: #10b981;
  --font-display: "Inter", sans-serif;
  --space-4: 1rem;
  --radius-md: 0.375rem;
}
```

## Tailwind Config Integration

```javascript
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        primary: { DEFAULT: "#3B82F6", 50: "#EFF6FF" },
        secondary: { DEFAULT: "#10B981" },
      },
      fontFamily: {
        display: ["Inter", "sans-serif"],
      },
    },
  },
};
```

## Consistency Checklist

### Visual
- [ ] Colors match brand palette
- [ ] Typography uses brand fonts
- [ ] Spacing follows brand scale
- [ ] Logo usage follows guidelines

### Voice
- [ ] Tone matches brand personality
- [ ] No forbidden phrases used
- [ ] Messaging aligns with brand values

### Technical
- [ ] CSS variables used throughout
- [ ] Components use design tokens
- [ ] Accessibility maintained
